This is a collection of the diaries and papers of Jean Scobie Davis. Davis kept
                    daily diaries from 1911 to 1984. She also kept travel journals and a few
                    scrapbooks. This collection also includes: family histories compiled by Davis;
                    autobiographical notes; correspondence with family and friends; photo albums;
                    and records of her work with women's prison and reformatories for teenagers.
